    "**<font color='green'>On Mac</font>**\n",
    "1.  Get a LaTeX distribution by downloading and installing MacTeX:  http://www.tug.org/mactex/. Select the largest possible file (the first download link) if at all possible, as this includes the libraries you will use and prevents you having to install them manually.  If your internet connection will not allow you to download this file, select the next largest.\n",
    "\n",
    "2.  MacTeX already includes a front-end called TeXShop so you're done and don't ned to do anything else.\n",
    "\n",
    "**<font color='green'>On a Windows PC</font>**\n",
    "1.  Get a LaTeX distribution by downloading and install MiKTeX:  https://miktex.org/\n",
    "\n",
    "2.  Get a front-end by downloading and installing TeXMaker:  http://www.xm1math.net/texmaker/\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "**<font color='green'>On Ubuntu, Fedora, and similar</font>**\n",
    "1.  TeXLive comes native in recent versions of Ubunto and Fedora, but if you happen to be running something really old, you can install it manually: http://www.tug.org/texlive/\n",
    "\n",
    "2.  Get a front-end by downloading and installing TeXMaker:  http://www.xm1math.net/texmaker/\n",
    "\n"
