    "## <font color='red'> Some basic and simple rules:</font> "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1. Most of the time, type normally.\n",
    "2. Words are separated by one or more spaces, paragraphs are separated by one or more lines. \n",
    "3. Some symbols such as **<font color='green'>\\$</font>** , **<font color='green'> &</font>**, **<font color='green'>#</font>**, and **<font color='green'>%</font>** need to be preceded by backslash **<font color='green'>\\</font>** to appear.\n",
    "4. Use \"%\" to comment your document directly. "
   ]
